Counteraction against Japan's Moves for Militarism Declared
 
.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, May 9 (KCNA) -- An inaugural ceremony of the anti-Japanese action network for peace in Northeast Asia took place at the Thapgol Park in Seoul on May 3, according to the south Korean Internet broadcasting service "Voice of People".
 Speakers at the ceremony including the permanent representative chairman of the Reunification Solidarity referred to the purpose of the formation of the organization, stating that Japan's moves for the restoration of militarism through its attempt to seize Tok Islet, the distortion of history, visit to the "Yasukuni Shrine" and other actions are unpardonable. .&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They declared that they would strongly counter Japan's moves for the restoration of militarism, reflecting the ardent desire of all the people to preserve peace in the Korean Peninsula and the rest of Northeast Asia. .&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A written inaugural declaration was read out at the ceremony. .&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It called for conducting a vigorous anti-Japanese struggle in solidarity with the civic and social organizations in the Asian region.

Implanting Militarism in Japan Denounced
 
.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, May 9 (KCNA) -- Papers Tuesday carry signed commentaries denouncing the intensified drive in Japan to inculcate the militarist idea of aggression into people's mind through the visit to the "Yasukuni Shrine".
 Ninety-six lawmakers of Japan affiliated with the "Meeting of Dietmen to Make All Visit Yasukuni Shrine" went to the shrine in group. When Asian countries voiced protest to this, the Japanese reactionaries tried to justify it, throwing together the balderdash that this is "an interference in internal affairs" and only some countries strain their nerves while others remain silent. .&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Branding this as a manifestation of militarist self-righteousness and aggressive psychology, the Rodong Sinmun analyst says: .&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 What the Japanese ruling quarters seek in the visit to the "Yasukuni Shrine" is to indoctrinate the Japanese people in militarist idea so they may carry forward the "will" of the forefathers who engaged themselves in aggression and war. .&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese reactionaries are going to great pains to din the militarist idea of aggression into the ears of the Japanese people, particularly the younger generation, through the visit to the shrine. .&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Asian people, who suffered shocking misfortunes and pains at the hands of the Japanese imperialists in the past, hope that such blood-stained history will not be repeated. That is the root cause of the opposition of Asian countries to the Japanese ruling quarters' visit to the shrine. .&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Nevertheless, the Japanese militarists zealously support the visit of the chief executive to the shrine and go to it in group, complaining of the just demand of Asian countries.
 Their visit to the shrine is intended to lay an ideological foundation for reinvasion. But they are seriously mistaken. They will pay dearly, if they persist in the visit to the shrine and race headlong to reinvasion, averting their eyes from the change of the times. .&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Minju Joson brands the recent visit to the "Yasukuni Shrine" by the Japanese reactionaries in group as a downright challenge to justice and human conscience and warns them not to act on impulse.

Anniversary of Victory in Great Patriotic War Observed
 
.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, May 9 (KCNA) -- The Korean people extend warm congratulations and friendly greetings to the Russian people on the 61st anniversary of their victory in the Great Patriotic War and sincerely wish them a rosier future, observes Rodong Sinmun Tuesday in a signed article.
  The existence of Russia, progress made by it and its dignity and honor would have been unthinkable without the shining victory won in the Patriotic War against the armed invasion of fascist Germany, the article notes, and goes on: .&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The war fought by the Soviet people taught the following important lessons: The first is that it is impossible for a country to win a war, much less defending sovereignty, security and peace of the country, unless it has powerful strength. The second is that a country should not harbor any illusion about the aggression forces' clarion rhetoric about "peace" but build up powerful military force by tightening its belt in order to win a victory of justice over injustice and that of peace over war. .&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Much water has flown under the bridge since the war between the Soviet Union and fascist Germany. But there still remains on earth the outdated force of imperialism and the danger of aggression and war still hovers. U.S. imperialism, the ringleader of imperialism, is unhesitatingly committing aggression of sovereign countries under the pretext of "combating terrorism" to realize its ambition to put the world under its domination. .&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The prevailing situation requires the countries aspiring after independence and peace to bolster their military muscle to avert a war and defend their sovereignty and security.

Wreaths Laid on Day of Russia's Victory in Patriotic War
.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, May 9 (KCNA) -- Staff members of the Russian embassy here placed a wreath before the Liberation Tower on Tuesday on the occasion of the 61st anniversary of Russia's victory in the great Patriotic War.
 Present at the wreath-laying ceremony were Ambassador Andrei Karlov and officials of the Russian embassy and diplomatic envoys of different countries and representatives of international organizations. .&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Amidst the playing of the wreath-laying music a wreath in the name of the Russian embassy was placed before the tower and the participants paid silent tribute to the fallen fighters of the Soviet Army. .&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They also laid a wreath and bouquets before the cemetery of fallen fighters of the Soviet Army in Sadong District, Pyongyang.

Efficient High-tech Goods Introduced into Economic Sector
.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, May 9 (KCNA) -- Efficient high-tech goods have been applied to various sectors of the national economy in the Democratic People's Republic of Korea.
 Among them are mechanical rotary packing ring apparatus, hydraulic bio-micromanipulator and pneumatic ore pulp delivery machine. .&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The mechanical rotary packing ring apparatus is applicable to various kinds of pumps, turbines, refrigerators, compressors and rolling stocks.  It prevents the loss of fluids including water, air and oil working under high pressure and temperature.
 The apparatus is paying off at the Pyongyang Children's Foodstuff Factory, Taedonggang Beer Factory, Taehongdan Potato-processing Factory and various other units. .&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It has been introduced on a trial and its quality authenticated in several countries, enjoying popularity among them. .&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The remote-controlled hydraulic bio-micromanipulator makes it possible to mechanically handle matters which are seen by a microscope of 250-600 magnifications. It is being used in the biological and medical fields with micron-sized substances as working objects. .&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The pneumatic ore pulp delivery machine based a new technology can transport highly-concentrated ore fluid up to a height of over 100 meters by pipeline. .&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It has been widely applied to mines, proving effective in doing away with the wastage of mineral resources and preventing environmental destruction and pollution.

Architectural Festival Held

.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, May 9 (KCNA) -- The sixth May 21 architectural festival was held here from May 4 to 9.
 It drew architects, construction technicians and teachers and researchers in the field of architecture and construction from across the country. It was divided into prize contests among designers of rural villages, modern urban and rural dwelling houses, street and garden lamps, and furniture, an architectural and construction symposium and a competition for the modernization of architectural and construction designing. .&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The festival received at least 320 designing entries, more than 150 scientific papers and over 40 programs for construction designing. .&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It was noteworthy in the designs for urban and rural dwelling houses and rural villages that they were laid out in a unique manner and new type roofs chosen for them and they were done in such a way as to protect ecological environment and make a rational use of renewable energy. 
 Designs for street and garden lamps served the purpose of more beautifully decorating streets, parks and recreation grounds and matched well the natural scenery, while ensuring economic profitability. .&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The architectural symposium was divided into more than 10 panels including architecture, structure, building materials, construction, city management and environmental engineering. Its participants heard valuable papers helpful to solving realistic problems arising in developing the country's architectural science and technology. .&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Participants of the festival also presented valuable programs helpful to developing the country's architectural and building science and technology by introducing the state-of-the-art IT means including a consultation and support system for architectural designing. .&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The festival closed with due ceremony at the People's Palace of Culture Tuesday.
 After the results of the festival were announced by the jury, best prize, excellent prize, festival prize and labor prize were awarded to the successful participants.

First Architectural Aesthetic Symposium Held

.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, May 9 (KCNA) -- The first architectural aesthetic symposium was held at the People's Palace of Culture Tuesday.
 The symposium clearly explained and proved the originality and vitality of leader Kim Jong Il's Juche-based idea of architecture, principled matters for developing the nation's architecture as required by the new century and ways to do so. .&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il authored famous work "Theory of Architectural Art" on May 21, Juche 80 (1991) in which he clarified the issue of fully applying the revolutionary view on the leader to architecture, the issue of creating Korean-style architecture, the issue of embodying the party spirit, the working class spirit and the popular spirit in architectural creation and properly combining the national peculiarity and modernity in it, and the issue of raising the quality of architecture and economic effectiveness as fundamental principles to govern the Juche-based architectural creation. .&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Pae Tal Jun, minister of State Construction Control, Tong Jong Ho, minister of Construction and Building Materials Industries, and many other speakers said that these principles indicate the most correct way for our architecture to actively contribute to the independent and creative life of the popular masses as they are most scientific and just principles meeting the requirements of the socialist society. They referred to the issues of strictly abiding by them. .&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  They stressed the need to establish the revolutionary view on the leader in the city construction and apply the popular spirit in it so as to systematically give face-lift to urban and rural villages as required by the times and as desired by the popular masses. They also underlined the need to fully meet the requirements of the formative artistic representation in the city lay-out and actively bring the flexible formation of main structures in step with it so that cities may win the admiration of the posterity. .&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They called for bringing about a great innovation in the overall field of building materials industry by stepping up the reconstruction and modernization of factories and enterprises in this field and keeping the production of modern ordinary building materials and finishing materials going at a high rate as required by the new century, etc. .&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They evinced their pledge to properly work out a master-plan of for the construction of the capital city of Pyongyang and push ahead with this construction under a long-term plan on its basis. They also said that they would rebuild all cities and rural villages on a modern basis and continue to push ahead with the work to create forests, improve rivers and streams and build roads, while dynamically stepping up the work to convert the capital city into greenery and woodland. .&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Present at the symposium were Choe Thae Bok, secretary of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea, Jon Sung Hun, vice-premier of the Cabinet, Cabinet members, and officials concerned, and designers, technicians, teachers and researchers in the fields of architecture, construction, building materials, city management, and land and environmental protection.
